00:16:35,145 --> 00:16:40,134
If that's the case, the first step we'll need to
take is to access the databank to get the information.

251
00:16:40,245 --> 00:16:42,250
What if the data isn't in the databank?

252
00:16:42,337 --> 00:16:43,655
It will be there somewhere.

253
00:16:43,789 --> 00:16:48,484
Data is stored on any adult who has been to
the hospital or taken a vocational aptitude test,

254
00:16:48,531 --> 00:16:51,797
along with all the students
undergoing ability development.

255
00:16:51,892 --> 00:16:54,707
Okay... but this is all still really confusing...

256
00:16:54,810 --> 00:16:57,788
How could using the Level Upper
reprogram somebody's brain waves?

257
00:16:57,813 --> 00:17:00,840
And moreover, how would doing that
raise somebody's ability level...?

258
00:17:00,983 --> 00:17:02,880
So much of this seems impossible.

259
00:17:02,905 --> 00:17:04,025
It's like a computer.

260
00:17:04,050 --> 00:17:06,244
Not even one of those will increase in performance that

261
00:17:06,269 --> 00:17:09,109
dramatically just because you're
running different software on it.

262
00:17:09,355 --> 00:17:11,550
Unless it's connected to a network, anyway.

263
00:17:11,796 --> 00:17:15,075
So a computer's performance
increases when connected to a network?

264
00:17:15,123 --> 00:17:17,682
Well, individually, there's no major improvement...

265
00:17:17,730 --> 00:17:21,202
But you can connect a lot of different
computers in a parallel network...

266
00:17:21,375 --> 00:17:23,586
then their computing power does increase.

267
00:17:23,626 --> 00:17:27,303
That's it... Whoever's behind this
is constructing a network of brains!

268
00:17:27,328 --> 00:17:28,854
And they're doing it with the Level Upper!

269
00:17:28,909 --> 00:17:30,564
Well, it is a possibility.

270
00:17:30,777 --> 00:17:31,845
But how does it work?

271
00:17:31,879 --> 00:17:34,125
What's connecting all of their brainwaves together?

272
00:17:34,228 --> 00:17:36,104
If I had to make a guess, then...

273
00:17:36,318 --> 00:17:38,368
maybe an AIM diffusion field...?

274
00:17:38,811 --> 00:17:42,514
All espers emit a force around
themselves without even being aware of it.

275
00:17:42,696 --> 00:17:44,581
If those were to be connected....

276
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:47,586
But you said espers do that unconsciously...

277
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:52,149
Besides, if we're comparing humans to computers,
wouldn't we all run different operating systems...?

278
00:17:52,479 --> 00:17:54,941
How would it be possible to link up together, then?

279
00:17:55,052 --> 00:17:58,269
Computers in a network also
have different operating systems;

280
00:17:58,333 --> 00:18:00,042
they even use different languages.

281
00:18:00,804 --> 00:18:04,047
But networks can be created by
putting certain protocols in place.

282
00:18:05,747 --> 00:18:09,258
So in this case, you're saying that a
particular person's brainwave pattern

283
00:18:09,283 --> 00:18:11,482
is serving as the protocol for the whole network?

284
00:18:11,546 --> 00:18:13,413
It's all speculation at this point.

285
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:16,273
Okay... and if a number of
brains were connected like that...

286
00:18:16,391 --> 00:18:19,664
they would be able to do an enormous amount of computing.

287
00:18:20,697 --> 00:18:24,671
So one person might have only a weak
ability, but by plugging into the network,

288
00:18:24,702 --> 00:18:28,803
the throughput of that ability would increase,
making the person significantly stronger.

289
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:32,535
Add to that the collective thought
patterns of espers who have the same talent,

290
00:18:32,598 --> 00:18:35,523
and you'd be able to manage
that ability much more efficiently.

291
00:18:35,562 --> 00:18:37,525
It would be an incredible boost in power.

292
00:18:37,588 --> 00:18:43,277
So my hypothesis is that all the brain activity of
the coma patients is being used to power this network.

293
00:18:44,848 --> 00:18:45,941
Hey, here we go!

294
00:18:46,161 --> 00:18:49,131
The brain patterns' agreement
rate is ninety... nine percent.

295
00:18:53,978 --> 00:18:54,787
This, too...

296
00:18:54,970 --> 00:18:55,938
and this.

297
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:58,386
These are all papers on synesthesia...

298
00:18:59,389 --> 00:19:00,306
but why?

299
00:19:03,409 --> 00:19:04,836
How impolite of you.

300
00:19:06,378 --> 00:19:10,151
Looking at somebody's research
papers without asking permission.

301
00:19:11,327 --> 00:19:13,576
Can... can it be true?

302
00:19:13,703 --> 00:19:14,927
Registrant name...

303
00:19:15,459 --> 00:19:16,710
Harumi Kiyama?!

304
00:19:17,516 --> 00:19:18,693
Uiharu!

305
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:20,449
What do you mean? What about her?

306
00:19:20,474 --> 00:19:23,325
She said earlier that she was
on her way to Dr. Kiyama's office!

307
00:19:23,350 --> 00:19:24,445
What's she doing?

308
00:19:26,034 --> 00:19:26,962
Uiharu!

309
00:19:28,673 --> 00:19:30,126
I'm not getting through to her.

310
00:19:30,151 --> 00:19:33,344
Contact Antiskill and have them
take the doctor into custody...

311
00:19:33,470 --> 00:19:35,830
but be sure to warn them. There might be a hostage.

312
00:19:35,891 --> 00:19:36,506
Right!

313
00:19:44,764 --> 00:19:45,797
You know something...?

314
00:19:46,011 --> 00:19:48,449
I've been wondering about this for a while now...

315
00:19:48,497 --> 00:19:50,658
What's with all the flowers in your hair...?

316
00:19:50,951 --> 00:19:53,675
Does it have something to do
with your ability as an esper?

317
00:19:53,739 --> 00:19:55,748
I don't see why I should answer your questions.

318
00:19:55,828 --> 00:19:57,194
But I have some for you...

319
00:19:57,266 --> 00:19:59,299
I want you to tell me about the Level Upper.

320
00:19:59,585 --> 00:20:01,230
Why have you done all of this...?

321
00:20:01,380 --> 00:20:03,606
What will happen to the people who are sick?

322
00:20:04,523 --> 00:20:06,359
You are full of questions...

323
00:20:06,445 --> 00:20:09,828
And yet you refuse to answer
the single question I asked of you.

324
00:20:10,018 --> 00:20:13,010
What do you get out of randomly
increasing someone's ability...?

325
00:20:13,279 --> 00:20:15,593
You raise their hopes, and then you put them in a coma?

326
00:20:16,196 --> 00:20:18,380
Saten's a kind, loving person.

327
00:20:19,890 --> 00:20:21,943
She doesn't deserve something like this.

328
00:20:23,312 --> 00:20:26,658
I have no interest at all in other people's abilities.

329
00:20:27,316 --> 00:20:30,598
My ultimate objective is much greater than that.

330
00:20:33,775 --> 00:20:35,000
I'm coming along, too.

331
00:20:35,025 --> 00:20:37,526
Although I don't normally like
getting civilians involved...

332
00:20:37,629 --> 00:20:40,535
having someone with your power around could be beneficial.

333
00:20:43,506 --> 00:20:44,706
Hold on, Sissy!

334
00:20:45,231 --> 00:20:47,687
Don't forget Uiharu's a member of Judgment.

335
00:20:47,785 --> 00:20:49,808
She can handle herself if she needs to.

336
00:20:51,991 --> 00:20:54,678
Probably... if she's lucky...

337
00:20:56,738 --> 00:20:58,571
It isn't that unlikely...

338
00:20:59,970 --> 00:21:02,322
Besides, Antiskill is getting involved, too.

339
00:21:02,347 --> 00:21:05,866
I doubt a scrawny scientist like her
will be able to do much against them.

340
00:21:06,048 --> 00:21:10,275
The lives of thousands of comatose
espers are in her hands as we speak.

341
00:21:11,325 --> 00:21:11,957
Plus...

342
00:21:12,235 --> 00:21:14,199
I've just got a bad feeling about this...

343
00:21:14,224 --> 00:21:17,473
You're right... This could be bad...
Which is why a Judgment officer...

344
00:21:22,352 --> 00:21:24,530
Are you in good enough shape to go into action?

345
00:21:24,578 --> 00:21:26,991
You mean you knew... about all my injuries?

346
00:21:27,079 --> 00:21:28,398
Yeah, of course I did.

347
00:21:31,696 --> 00:21:34,213
You may be strong, but I'm still the older one here.

348
00:21:34,879 --> 00:21:36,143
It's been a rough week...

349
00:21:36,365 --> 00:21:38,097
so you can turn to your Sissy.

350
00:21:42,671 --> 00:21:43,945
Thank you, Sissy.

351
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:33,412
I had a great time today...

352
00:23:33,682 --> 00:23:36,119
And I think I'll finish by undressing for the preview...

353
00:23:36,206 --> 00:23:36,885
Next time...

354
00:23:36,909 --> 00:23:37,992
Keep your clothes on!

355
00:23:38,071 --> 00:23:40,182
And get ready, 'cause I'm taking you down!

